<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could just imagine letting=C2=A0companies=
=C2=A0precisely customize how their stock trades:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Your stock can trade 24 hours a day, =
or just regular trading hours, or one auction a day, or one big liquidity e=
vent per quarter, or only on specific dates that you choose at your discret=
ion.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The trading price of your sto=
ck could be publicly reported in real time, or with a delay, or not at all.=
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">You can disclose news and audited=
 GAAP financial statements=C2=A0publicly to everyone, or only to your curre=
nt investors, or you can keep everything=C2=A0secret.</li>=09<li style=3D"m=
argin-bottom: 5px;">You can let anyone buy your stock, or only =E2=80=9C<a =
href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35325192.257342/aHR0c=
HM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9lZHVjYXRpb24vY2FwaXRhbHJhaXNpbmcvYnVpbGRpbmctYmxvY2tz=
