<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you start a hedge fund and it goes well and=
 you have good performance and gather a lot of assets, you will become a bi=
g-time hedge fund manager, and then I suppose you face a choice. Do you ins=
titutionalize the fund, so that you can eventually step back and transition=
 to new leadership without a hiccup, or do you build a cult of personality =
around yourself as a singular genius who controls every aspect of the firm=
=E2=80=99s operations, so that you feel important but can never leave? I fe=
el like Ray Dalio at Bridgewater Associates is unusual in that he somehow d=
id the maximum amount of=C2=A0<em>both.</em>=C2=A0Bridgewater is a huge aut=
omated institution that has operated without Dalio for a while now, but als=
o few companies have ever been built more in the image of one person. Anywa=
y the Financial Times <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/35325192.257342/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvYjRlYTE0NTYtNTJkOC0=
0MmQzLWFhYTMtZjRiNmI4MTg0Mzhl/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBeb473c5f" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
checks in with the new guy</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bridgewater Associates=E2=80=99 new chief exec=
utive Nir Bar Dea said he had overhauled the hedge fund after just a year i=
n charge, in a bid to restore the firm=E2=80=99s investment performance and=
 mark a break from founder Ray Dalio.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEverything has to get rewired,=E2=80=
=9D Bar Dea told the Financial Times. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s like taking a b=
rain and a heart out of a human and then planting a new brain and a new hea=
rt.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re proud of Ray being a pa=
rt of our history,=E2=80=9D he said. =E2=80=9CBut it=E2=80=99s also true th=
at Ray is . . . his own person and has his own set of goals. He does a lot =
of things outside of Bridgewater and that=E2=80=99s great. We want that for=
 him. And then we need our independence.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Okay. The management committee at D.E. Shaw ne=
ver went around being like =E2=80=9Cwe had to murder David Shaw and remove =
his heart,=E2=80=9D but Bridgewater is an unusual place. Even now:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bar Dea accepts that Bridgewater=E2=80=99s pur=
suit of what he calls =E2=80=9Cabsolute truth=E2=80=9D is not for everyone.=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CPeople almost self-select themselves =
to be in a place that puts truth above everything else,=E2=80=9D he said. B=
ar Dea has previously said that the firm=E2=80=99s success is based on the =
=E2=80=9Ccore idea of a group of people that want to be excellent so much t=
hat they=E2=80=99re going to be living in a state of uncomfortableness=E2=
=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still, the 42-year-old maintains that there ar=
e key ways in which Bridgewater=E2=80=99s culture has changed under his lea=
dership.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Feedback is predominantly given by junior empl=
oyees to more senior ones, which is a =E2=80=9Cday and night change=E2=80=
=9D from when he joined =E2=80=94 back then =E2=80=9Cthe flow of that feedb=
ack [was] almost entirely going from the top down=E2=80=9D, he said.=C2=A0<=
/p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right right see at a lot of hedge funds the wa=
y it works is that the junior analyst says =E2=80=9Cwe should buy this stoc=
k=E2=80=9D and the experienced portfolio manager is like =E2=80=9Cno we sho=
uldn=E2=80=99t, here=E2=80=99s why,=E2=80=9D and the junior analyst learns =
over time what stocks to buy. Whereas at Bridgewater =E2=80=9Cfeedback is p=
redominantly given by junior employees to more senior ones,=E2=80=9D becaus=
e it is pursuing some higher goal than teaching the employees how to make m=
oney in financial markets.</p>
