that they <em>played</em> for the Yankees. Maybe auction off a few roster s=
pots? There is a balance to be struck here: I suspect you could find a few =
hedge fund managers who would pay a lot of money to be Lionel Messi=E2=80=
=99s teammate for a game, but if Inter Miami fielded a team made up of the =
11 highest bidders then most of the glamour would be lost. (I would still w=
atch this?)</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Naturally readers emailed me=C2=A0the sports i=
n which this system actually exists. The main ones are bridge and car=C2=A0=
racing. In car racing, Braden Williams pointed out:=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In high-level Endurance racing, th=
